HEADWORD: Cinchonine
<hw>Cin"cho*nine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Cinchona</er>: cf. F. <ets>cinchonine</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>One of the quinine group of alkaloids isomeric
with and resembling cinchonidine; -- called also
<altname>cinchonia</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

